However, Mr Johnson says the beating was retribution for the theft of seven chainsaws by the man

He told WMC Action News, which tracked him down: 'The man is not homeless, the man used to live with my brother.

'He's a good friend of mine. I own my own tree business, he worked for me for a long time. He stole all of my equipment.'

Mr Johnson says the panhandler stole seven of the chainsaws that he needs to run his family's business and attacking the man was retribution.

The TV station showed the footage to Memphis panhandlers, who were horrified.

