Mr Johnson does have a criminal history, though his most recent charge was 2008.

Memphis Police have issued an arrest warrant for Mr Johnson for Simple Assault, reports WREG Memphis. 

He told the station it was 'worth it.' 

'I don’t think it was wrong at all because that’s what used to happen. You know? But I don’t…I do agree that it’s against the law. You know what I mean? Probably not legal,Johnson said. 

